            {
              "id": "a7419fd1-d235-3486-8933-e47678171974",
              "name": "Insecure Usage Of Temp File Or Directory",
              "helpUri": "https://www.glog.ai/",
              "help": {
                "text": "",
                "markdown": "## Description\n\nInsecure temporary file handling. Writing directly to a predictable path under /tmp can let another local user pre-create, replace, or symlink that file before your code opens it.\n\nIn Python, using open(\"/tmp/acme.csr\", \"wb\") for temporary output is unsafe because the filename is fixed and the shared temporary directory is writable by other users. That can cause unintended overwrite, disclosure, or redirection of sensitive data such as certificate signing requests. Use the tempfile module to create a unique file securely with restricted permissions, and avoid hard-coded names in shared temp locations.\n\nFor this sink, create the temporary file with tempfile.NamedTemporaryFile or tempfile.mkstemp, write the CSR data to the returned file handle, and clean it up after use. If the file must persist after closing, use delete=False and remove it explicitly when finished.\n\n## Mitigation Advice\n\nDo not construct temporary file paths manually in shared directories such as /tmp. Use Python's tempfile APIs so the file is created atomically with a unique name and restrictive permissions. Keep the file handle returned by the secure creation call instead of reopening a predictable path. If temporary data is sensitive, minimize its lifetime, delete it as soon as possible, and prefer in-memory handling when practical. If a specific directory is required, ensure it is application-controlled and not writable by untrusted users.\n\n## Source Code Fix Recommendation\n\n~~~python\nimport os\nimport tempfile\n\nfd, temp_path = tempfile.mkstemp(suffix=\".csr\")\ntry:\n    with os.fdopen(fd, \"wb\") as out:\n        out.write(csr_bytes)\n\n    # use temp_path as needed\nfinally:\n    if os.path.exists(temp_path):\n        os.remove(temp_path)\n~~~\n\n## Library Dependencies\n\n~~~python\nimport os\nimport tempfile\n~~~\n\n## References\n\n- [CWE-377: Insecure Temporary File](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/377.html)\n- [CWE-378: Creation of Temporary File With Insecure Permissions](https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/378.html)\n- [Python tempfile — Generate temporary files and directories securely](https://docs.python.org/3/library/tempfile.html)\n- [OWASP: Insecure Temporary File](https://owasp.org/www-community/vulnerabilities/Insecure_Temporary_File)\n"
              },
              "properties": {
                "cwe": [
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-377",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/377.html"
                  },
                  {
                    "id": "CWE-378",
                    "url": "https://cwe.mitre.org/data/definitions/378.html"
                  }
                ],
                "kind": "FAIL",
                "security-severity": "5.0",
                "tags": [
                  "security",
                  "CWE-377",
                  "CWE-378"
                ]
              }
